22/07/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- During a closed-door session Wednesday (21 July), parliament approved a report on the results of the Strategic Defence Review. 
The document outlines defence reforms to be implemented by 2015, including army modernisation, staff downsizing and the development of a professional army. 
After the passage of the report, Bulgarian Army Chief of General Staff General Nikola Kolev released a statement saying the army staff would be reduced from 45,000 to 39,000 in the next ten years. 
(Trud, 24 Chasa - 22/07/04)
